x4freetext: /By authors/ Measurements of inelastic scattering
cross sections are also useful for testing statistical
model codes. We have included Cu-63(p,p`+g)Cu-63
in the present work, this being the only (p,p`+g)
reaction for which there was measurement yield.
/By authors/ The cross sections for Cu-63(p,p(i)) for
i=1-5 were based on observation of the ground state
gamma ray from (p,p(i)+g) for i=1,2,4,5, and of the
3-2 gamma ray fop i=3. The branching ratios applicable
to these gamma ray were 100% for i=1 and 2.72% for
i=4.80% for i=5, and 16% for i=3. The (p,p(3)+g)
ground state gamma ray was obscured by that from
Cu-63(p,a(1)+g)Ni-60 and could not be used.
/By compiler/ The authors have not reported the
energy levels.
